    <item>
      <title>Intelligence Brief: The 2026 Zero-Day Surge &amp; Legacy Debt</title>
      <link>https://whimsical-macaron-cef883.netlify.app/posts/april-2026-intel-brief/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 09:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://whimsical-macaron-cef883.netlify.app/posts/april-2026-intel-brief/</guid>
      <description>A deep dive into the April 2026 vulnerability landscape, from SharePoint zero-days to the persistent threat of legacy technical debt.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Two-Front War: Zero-Days and Legacy Debt</title>
      <link>https://whimsical-macaron-cef883.netlify.app/posts/first-post/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 07:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://whimsical-macaron-cef883.netlify.app/posts/first-post/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The cybersecurity landscape in April 2026 is presenting a unique challenge for defenders: a &amp;ldquo;two-front war.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;the-modern-threat-2026-zero-days&#34;&gt;The Modern Threat: 2026 Zero-Days&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recent Patch Tuesday updates have revealed critical vulnerabilities across the board. Notably, a &lt;strong&gt;Microsoft SharePoint zero-day&lt;/strong&gt; was actively exploited before a patch could be deployed, and &lt;strong&gt;Adobe Acrobat Reader&lt;/strong&gt; required an emergency fix for &lt;strong&gt;CVE-2026-34621&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;the-persistent-threat-legacy-debt&#34;&gt;The Persistent Threat: Legacy Debt&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Simultaneously, CISA&amp;rsquo;s latest KEV update shows that attackers are still leveraging decade-old exploits. This proves that technical debt is not just a performance issue—it&amp;rsquo;s a security catastrophe.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
